subject: Baseball
Free Agents (Sports)
lead_paragraph: Jason Jennings, a Dallas native who grew up watching Nolan Ryan pitch for Texas, was introduced as the newest addition to the Rangers’ rotation. Jennings, a free-agent right-hander, agreed to a one-year deal worth $4 million. Jennings, 29, is coming off an injury-plagued season in Houston, where he was 2-9 with a career-worst 6.45 earned run average. He missed three months with elbow problems.
